{
  "title": "Gestures",
  "href": "http://www.google.com/design/spec/patterns/gestures.html",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "intro",
      "html": "<p><strong>Mobile only</strong></p><p>Gestures are divided into <strong>Touch Mechanics</strong>&#xA0;(what your fingers do on the screen) and <strong>Touch Activities</strong>&#xA0;(results of specific gestures). &#xA0;</p><p>A touch mechanic (such as swipe) may have multiple results (such as enable/disable), depending on the context. A touch activity (zoom in) may be achieved through multiple touch mechanics (pinch open, double touch, etc.). </p><p>The <a href=\"http://www.google.com/design/spec/patterns/gestures.html#gestures-drag-swipe-or-fling-details\">Drag, Swipe, and Fling</a> touch activities are covered in more detail due to their highly contextual results.</p>"
    },
    {
